your job is to create sensible bead tasks from this description:
create a bash script called main.sh that calls all scripts in the scripts directory then sleep for 30 minutes. do this in an endless Loop.
in the scripts directory create the following scripts:
- update_fixer.sh: loops through all repositories in the repo directory (adjustable via config located in the root directory of this repository) and does in a Loop over all renovate branches the following:
  - git fetch
  - git reset --hard
  - git clean
  - make test: if this command fails run opencode cli with the instruction to fix the branch that contains updates to dependecnies und push them to the branch
